<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Mortonia utahensis </i> is a sclerophyllous, intermountain shrub occurring in the Mojave Desert, Southeastern Great Basin, and Colorado Plateau regions. Its branching stems are whitish, and its leaves are thickened, curved upwards and concave. <br/>
<br/>
This alliance is found primarily on skeletal rocky slopes of various aspects, with parent material typically being limestone. It is related to other calciphilic alliances in mid-elevation Mojave Desert including <i>Coleogyne ramosissima</i> and<i>Purshia stansburiana</i>. </div>
</div>

    
	
	
