    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Ad, Aj). Stands occur in the Funeral Mountains and the Clark Mountain Range on rocky, limestone slopes.</li>
        
            <li><b>Southeastern Great Basin</b> (341Fd). The species has been documented from the southeastern Great Basin, including the Grapevine Mountains, where stands are likely.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> While this alliance has impacts from non-native plant invasions, roads, droughts, and past mining, various stands are protected in national parks and preserves. </div>
</div>

    

    

